Introduction to the Savory Snacks Market
Savory snacks, known for their salty or spicy flavors, have become an integral part of modern snacking habits. These snacks are manufactured using a variety of ingredients such as vegetables, fruits, nuts, grains, and seasonings, offering a rich source of nutrients, minerals, vitamins, and fibers. The global savory snacks market is driven by increasing consumer demand for convenient and healthy snacking options, coupled with rising disposable incomes and evolving lifestyles.
Definition of Savory Snacks
Savory snacks are food products characterized by their salty or spicy flavor profiles, contrasting with sweet snacks. They are typically consumed in small quantities between meals and include popular variants such as potato and corn chips, popcorn, pretzels, meat snacks, nuts, and seeds. These snacks are not only convenient but also provide essential nutrients, making them a popular choice among consumers seeking quick energy boosts.
